[Abdominal aneurysms: long-term results].

[Article in Dutch]

Noyez L, Nevelsteen A, Suy R, Daenen W, Stalpaert G.

437 patients who underwent surgery for abdominal aortic aneurysm have been 
studied. Of these, 206 patients (medium age 63 years) had elective surgery, 231 
patients (medium age 73 years) had acute surgery. The five-year survival rate 
was 65% for the elective group and 40% for the acute group, but these 
percentages are influenced by the perioperative mortality. When the survival 
