syndrome.

Donnenfeld AE, Conard KA, Roberts NS, Borns PF, Zackai EH.

A male fetus with decreased calvarial mineralization and suspected omphalocele 
was identified prenatally in a woman with oligohydramnios and Melnick-Needles 
syndrome (MNS). At autopsy, exophthalmos, prune belly sequence with urethal 
atresia and megacystis, tetralogy of Fallot, atrioventricular canal defect, and 
